  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2018-05-09T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Perioperative Reduction of Opioids Act or the PRO Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) to convene a technical expert panel to recommend ways to reduce opioid use in surgical settings and best practices for pain management, specifically during the perioperative (pre-operative through post-operative) period.\n\nHHS must also report on diagnosis-related group codes that have the highest volume of surgeries and the availability of associated data regarding post-operative opioid use, including prescription patterns and rates of consumption."
  }, 
